            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "No, please keep to the scope as written here; this is deliberate. The reason for sticking to tree-sitter captures (not highlight groups!) is\n1. documentation and usability: these are documented and _language-independent_.\n2. performance and code complexity: unlike legacy syntax, treesitter API allows very efficient extraction of _all_ regions corresponding to a given capture.\n\nAnd the main goal here is _replacing_, not searching, so `:s` is the main target; this keeps the feature clearly scoped without having to entangle it all over the codebase for these other commands. Anything else can be handled as a follow-up, if necessary.",
